<a name="5286"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Audit Confirms Record International Attendance at 2011 CES</div>
<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/2011AuditSummary_cvr_150.jpg" width=150 height=194>Coming out of the 2011 CES, there was no doubt that attendance was up. Throngs of people were buzzing about the show. Now, the numbers are in to prove it! Up 30 percent from last year, international attendance at the 2011 CES (Jan. 6-9, 2011) set a new record for the show’s 45-year history. Industry professionals from outside the U.S. came in at an impressive 31,677, according to an independent audit performed by Veris Consulting LLC. The audit also confirms CES’ status as the world’s largest consumer technology tradeshow and North America’s largest annual tradeshow of any kind. Overall, the 2011 International CES welcomed 149,529 technology attendees during its four day run. 
<P></P>
<P>View more information and detailed breakouts of attendance and see what you can expect for 2012.&nbsp; <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/docs/2011AuditSummary.pdf" target=_blank>Read the 2011 CES Audit Summary</A>.<BR></P>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="5285"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">What’s your Strategy in China?</div>
<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/SINOCES_LOGO_180.jpg" width=180 height=60>The Chinese market will account for 15 percent of global consumer electronics (CE) retail revenue in 2011 with revenue expected to top $144 billion USD*,&nbsp; which is more than South America and the Middle East combined! Are you positioned to capitalize on this market? <BR><BR>Join more than 500 exhibitors from China and abroad that will showcase the CE latest products and technologies at <A href="http://cesweb.org./events/D27CAB76E49641B1950E77DF6CA09A6F.htm " target=_blank>SINOCES</A>, China’s largest exhibition for consumer technology. SINOCES will take place July 7-10, 2011, in Qingdao, China. <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/shared_files/edm/2012CES/ExhibComm/Alerts/SINOCES/fact_sheet.pdf" target=_blank>Learn more</A>.<BR><BR>SINOCES provides a platform for leading retailers from around the world to see the latest products from global CE manufacturers and service providers. If your company is in China or looking to expand to China, this is event is a must for 2011. <BR><BR>Contact Kristen Stake at <A href="mailto:kstake@CE.org">kstake@CE.org</A> to learn how you can participate in China’s premier event for industry professionals.<BR><BR>SINOCES is a collaboration between the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)®, producer of the International CES and the Qingdao Municipal People’s Government. <BR><BR><EM>*According to CEA/GfK Market Research<BR></EM>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="5288"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">It’s Almost Time to Update Your Directory Listing </div>
<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/2011_CES_Directory_Cover.JPG" width=119 height=160>Calling all 2012 International CES exhibitors!&nbsp; It’s almost that time of year for you to review and approve your company data coming live in early July on the exhibitor directory on <A href="http://www.cesweb.org">CESweb.org</A>. This important step in verifying your company information ensures that attendees viewing your online directory company listing (and later this fall, your company listing on the official interactive floor plan) are seeing the most up-to-date company info. More details to follow in the coming weeks!&nbsp; <BR><BR>If, when an attendee is viewing your online listing, you want to make a lasting impression, take a minute now to <A href="http://www.mapyourshow.com/info/CES_2012_MarketingOpps.pdf" target=_blank>review the digital marketing packages</A>. They’ve been designed to engage your audience, distinguish your company among your competitive field and elevate you from the 2,800 other exhibitors. <A href="mailto: brett@mapyourshow.com">Contact Brett</A> to learn more.<BR>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="5287"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Exhibitor PR Contact Information </div>
<br />

<EM>Leverage the CES PR tools and resources before, during and after the 2012 International CES by submitting your PR contact information. <BR></EM><BR>To ensure media find you at CES, please take a moment to list your company’s PR contact when you are updating your directory listing information. We will send out an email informing you when you can go in and make your updates. We will direct any media inquiries we receive regarding your company or products to the individual you indicate. The contact information will be available only to registered CES media.&nbsp; It is required that you go to your Exhibitor Directory Listing to add/update your PR Contact information.<BR><BR>Also, the Exhibitor PR Newsletter will be sent out to all PR contacts on the first Wednesday of every month starting in August.<BR><BR>Questions? Contact Allison Fried at <A href="mailto:afried@CE.org">afried@CE.org</A>.<BR>
