    <td bgcolor="#1B3D85" class="columnsubhead"><div align="center">A Message From </div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td>
    <p align="center"><img src="/images/content/Michelle_Griffin.jpg" alt="Karen Chupka"><br>
    <span class="smallText">
    <strong>Michelle Griffin</strong><br>
   Sr. Manager, Exhibitor Marketing</p>
    <hr align="center" width="90%" size="1" noshade color="#999999">
    <!-- article start -->
    <p><strong>Welcome to the Exhibitor’s Source Newsletter </strong><br> 
by Michelle Griffin</p>
    <p>So, you’ve signed up for space for the 2012 CES. Now what? That’s easy…start planning! Even though the show is in January, it’s never too early to start information gathering and learning all there is to know about CES. For instance, did you know that this year’s show is running on a Tuesday–Friday schedule? Or that this year’s keynote presentations have moved back to The Venetian? It’s a big show with tons of information, and without a plan, it can be overwhelming. The best place to start is with your monthly Exhibitor’s Source Newsletter.<BR><BR>The Exhibitor’s Source Newsletter is a great go-to for all information regarding CES in that particular month. Here, you will find show updates, promotional opportunities, award program info and -- most importantly -- critical operational and logistics information and support. You’ll receive your newsletter the first Tuesday of every month. <BR><BR>If you can’t get around to reading the newsletter, you can also follow CES on Facebook, LinkedIn and Twitter. Our Marketing and Operations teams will post updates and deadlines as they approach. It is another good source to keep you in the loop on all that is going on at the 2012 CES.&nbsp; <BR><BR>After great success in 2011, we’re pumped for the 2012 show and look forward to what all of you have in store. Every year, CES gets better and better, and we have you, our esteemed exhibitors, to thank. This year’s show floor will have some exciting new additions like the Eureka! Park TechZone and PMA@CES, which will both be featured at The Venetian along with our Unveiled Las Vegas event, keynote presentations and the 2012 Innovations Design and Engineering Awards Showcase. Returning to the show floor will be popular TechZones like Connected Home Appliances, Broadband Communications, Gaming Showcase and the iLounge Pavilion. While still seven months out from the show, our attendees are already giddy with excitement.
<P></P>
<P>Remember, be sure to read the Exhibitor’s Source Newsletter. You don’t want to miss any opportunities for great discounts and programs as well as contests and other ways to receive free exposure for your company. If you would like another member of your team added to our Exhibitor’s Source Newsletter mailing list, please e-mail me at <A href="mailto:mgriffin@CE.org">mgriffin@CE.org</A>, and I will add them to our distribution. Thanks again, and let’s get going on another amazing year!</P></p>
    <!-- article end -->
    </span>
    </td>
</tr>
